Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{}, season with @salt and @ground black pepper, sprinkle over the @roasted white sesame seeds{5%grams}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, in a large #bowl{}, combine the @rice vinegar{15%ml}, @sugar{1%tsp} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing. Season with @salt and @ground black pepper.

Add the @coleslaw mix{120%grams}, toss together, then set aside.

About 10 mins before the chips are ready, heat a drizzle of @olive oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @vegetable gyozas{1%pack} and fry until golden on the bottom, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Reduce the heat to medium-low, add @water{1%tbsp} to the pan and immediately cover with a #lid{} or some #foil{}.

Cook until the gyozas are piping hot, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Once the gyoza are ready, remove the pan from the heat, remove the lid and drizzle over the @gochujang paste{30%grams} and @honey{1%tbsp}.

Turn the gyozas so they're nicely coated in the glaze.

Just before you're ready to serve, add the @baby leaf mix{20%grams} to the coleslaw and toss together.

When everything's ready, transfer the gyozas to your plates. Drizzle over some of the @mayonnaise{64%grams} and sprinkle on the @crispy onions{1%sachet}.

Serve with the slaw salad and sesame chips, along with the remaining mayo for dipping.

Enjoy!